flowRoot.flowPara: The open-source software GMT is widely used is the Earth Sciences. It is written in C and provides an API that other programs can access. The API has been used to create interfaces for Matlab and Julia. We are building a Python interface for GMT called GMT/Python. The popularity of Python in the geosciences is growing because of its
simplicity and powerful libraries. Our goal is to
Develop a modern software (Python 3.5+ and GMT6 only) .
Make GMT easier to use and more accessible to new users.
Create an interface that is familiar to current Python users.
Code should be readable and immediately understandable.
Integrate with the existing scientific Python libraries.
Support for Jupyter notebooks and some interactive plots.
Maintain complete documentation and automated test.
Provide a welcoming environment for new contributors.

GMT/Python is still in early stages of development. ~70% of the basic functionality is implemented but GMT has many options and commands. Our project is open-source and we welcome the help of the Earth Science community. Anyone can contribute, regardless of skill level. We need ideas, bug reports and examples as well as code.
